1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,000
https://slama.dev/comeback/

2
00:00:05,650 --> 00:00:07,760
So, little girl, you'll run to the store.

3
00:00:07,760 --> 00:00:08,700
I already went.

4
00:00:08,920 --> 00:00:10,020
You'll clean up at home.

5
00:00:10,060 --> 00:00:11,120
I always do that.

6
00:00:11,500 --> 00:00:12,740
You'll count the sales.

7
00:00:13,080 --> 00:00:13,980
Did you sell anything?

8
00:00:14,180 --> 00:00:14,600
No.

9
00:00:15,650 --> 00:00:17,660
Well then, the sales won't be a problem.

10
00:00:18,150 --> 00:00:21,550
And you'll help me with Ozzak.

11
00:00:21,850 --> 00:00:23,350
What happened now?

12
00:00:24,560 --> 00:00:26,040
Praise the Lord Jesus, hail.

13
00:00:26,120 --> 00:00:27,040
Forever and ever, Uncle.

14
00:00:27,850 --> 00:00:30,520
Yesterday he was supposed to close up, and instead he fell asleep again.

15
00:00:30,520 --> 00:00:32,940
Good afternoon, bro, how'd you sleep?

16
00:00:33,100 --> 00:00:35,040
Great, I drooled like a rose, like a rose.

17
00:00:35,140 --> 00:00:36,700
And I even guarded the place for you.

18
00:00:38,750 --> 00:00:39,350
See, I even guard the place for you.

19
00:00:48,050 --> 00:00:50,190
Exactly, this is what's killing our sales.

20
00:00:50,450 --> 00:00:53,150
He does it all the time, why does it suddenly bother you so much?

21
00:00:54,950 --> 00:00:56,350
He's getting better at it.

22
00:00:59,150 --> 00:01:00,450
So say something to him.

23
00:01:01,150 --> 00:01:02,200
And who's the boss here?

24
00:01:02,200 --> 00:01:02,740
You are.

25
00:01:05,250 --> 00:01:05,960
Then deal with it.

26
00:01:06,250 --> 00:01:08,250
I'm going to check on the washing machine.

27
00:01:08,350 --> 00:01:08,890
Bye.

28
00:01:09,380 --> 00:01:10,020
Bye.

29
00:01:48,050 --> 00:01:49,350
For God's sake, what is that?

30
00:01:49,550 --> 00:01:50,350
That's Eddie.

31
00:01:51,650 --> 00:01:53,050
The Iron Maiden mascot.

32
00:01:54,250 --> 00:01:55,630
Have you lost your mind again?

33
00:01:55,850 --> 00:01:59,930
I wanted people to come in and feel like spending, not have a heart attack.

34
00:01:59,930 --> 00:02:01,790
Relax, bro, this is a sure thing.

35
00:02:02,370 --> 00:02:03,810
Quality sells itself.

36
00:02:04,750 --> 00:02:10,990
Tell me, sweetie, what is this?

37
00:02:11,390 --> 00:02:13,590
Easy, grandma, it's just a puppet.

38
00:02:14,150 --> 00:02:15,570
No, no, not that one.

39
00:02:15,950 --> 00:02:16,590
This one.

40
00:02:18,550 --> 00:02:20,250
Well, that's our salesman.

41
00:02:20,850 --> 00:02:24,350
He looks like the devil.

42
00:02:24,520 --> 00:02:25,340
Thanks, grandma.

43
00:02:25,340 --> 00:02:30,050
Well, I'm also a salesman, so what would you like?

44
00:02:30,250 --> 00:02:40,150
Of course, Highway to Hell.

45
00:02:40,550 --> 00:02:44,650
Angus Young's got a killer guitar riff on that, that's the one.

46
00:02:44,740 --> 00:02:45,260
Really?

47
00:02:46,420 --> 00:02:50,280
And does it also sing about a path through a blooming avenue?

48
00:02:50,440 --> 00:02:52,740
No way, don't worry, there's nothing like that on it.

49
00:02:52,760 --> 00:02:54,380
This is honest metal.

50
00:02:54,700 --> 00:02:55,660
What is it then?

51
00:02:56,100 --> 00:02:57,260
Eva and Vasek.

52
00:02:57,950 --> 00:02:59,650
That's probably what you meant, right?

53
00:03:00,870 --> 00:03:01,390
Certainly.

54
00:03:02,150 --> 00:03:06,950
Little Eva and Little Vasek.

55
00:03:09,850 --> 00:03:12,190
Quality sells itself.

56
00:03:13,050 --> 00:03:14,950
Wimp, I almost had her.

57
00:03:15,150 --> 00:03:15,850
Ozzak.

58
00:03:15,910 --> 00:03:18,350
The customer is king, does that mean anything to you?

59
00:03:18,490 --> 00:03:20,630
No, because my only king is Rock'n'Roll.

60
00:03:20,750 --> 00:03:23,630
Good for you, because my king is the installment plan.

61
00:03:23,650 --> 00:03:25,530
Do you know what happens if we can't pay this off?

62
00:03:25,750 --> 00:03:25,870
No.

63
00:03:28,080 --> 00:03:28,880
Me neither.

64
00:03:29,460 --> 00:03:31,900
But unlike you, at least it gives me anxiety.

65
00:03:37,850 --> 00:03:43,450
Listen, bro, your alphabetical system isn't very clear.

66
00:03:44,350 --> 00:03:45,650
What's unclear about it?

67
00:03:46,250 --> 00:03:48,650
Like the fact that it's not in alphabetical order at all.

68
00:03:52,280 --> 00:03:53,500
Hello, Mr. Pacovsky.

69
00:03:53,680 --> 00:03:54,700
Hey, Lexa.

70
00:03:55,270 --> 00:03:56,210
Hi, Mr. Ozzak.

71
00:03:56,390 --> 00:03:57,110
Hey, kid.

72
00:03:57,430 --> 00:03:58,170
Is Iva here?

73
00:03:59,130 --> 00:04:00,470
Dude, check this out.

74
00:04:01,150 --> 00:04:02,590
New Sabbath greatest hits coming out.

75
00:04:02,590 --> 00:04:03,250
Really?

76
00:04:03,250 --> 00:04:06,850
Man, the best-of of all the best-ofs.

77
00:04:07,050 --> 00:04:08,350
That'll be a blast.

78
00:04:08,350 --> 00:04:09,670
I'll go see her upstairs then.

79
00:04:09,670 --> 00:04:12,850
I have to order that right away, it'll sell itself.

80
00:04:13,470 --> 00:04:13,990
Goodbye.

81
00:04:17,670 --> 00:04:18,450
What is it?

82
00:04:18,450 --> 00:04:22,350
Ozzak, can you please tell me how many copies of the old one sold?

83
00:04:22,790 --> 00:04:24,130
I don't remember.

84
00:04:24,510 --> 00:04:24,690
No?

85
00:04:25,350 --> 00:04:26,550
Then let me tell you.

86
00:04:27,050 --> 00:04:28,270
A grand total of two.

87
00:04:28,550 --> 00:04:34,650
One was taken by you, and the other by some little runt who looks a lot like Lexa here.

88
00:04:36,150 --> 00:04:37,050
Goodbye.

89
00:04:37,190 --> 00:04:37,570
See ya.

90
00:04:39,250 --> 00:04:46,050
So, no Sabbath will be ordered. We're buying Gott and Vondráčková, because they'll at least pay the rent.

91
00:04:47,550 --> 00:04:51,550
Why can you sell records by your friends but I can't sell records by mine?

92
00:04:52,050 --> 00:04:57,650
Ozzak, just because you wear Ozzy Osbourne on your t-shirt doesn't mean you're friends.

93
00:05:00,100 --> 00:05:00,620
No.

94
00:05:04,330 --> 00:05:05,070
Good day.

95
00:05:06,130 --> 00:05:06,850
Good day.

96
00:05:07,450 --> 00:05:08,250
Greetings, told you.

97
00:05:14,020 --> 00:05:16,320
So, sir, do you know why we're here?

98
00:05:16,320 --> 00:05:19,820
I have no idea, are you interested in something special?

99
00:05:20,250 --> 00:05:21,050
I'd say so.

100
00:05:21,750 --> 00:05:22,850
Mr. Pacovsky, you owe Mr. Hajek 100,000 crowns.

101
00:05:25,310 --> 00:05:26,710
And Mr. Hajek doesn't what?

102
00:05:28,150 --> 00:05:29,950
Mr. Hajek doesn't like that.

103
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:32,280
But I'll obviously pay him back.

104
00:05:32,520 --> 00:05:34,660
Look, you have a really nice shop.

105
00:05:35,550 --> 00:05:40,850
And you surely wouldn't want some bad people coming in and doing something to it.

106
00:05:41,050 --> 00:05:41,950
Woohoo!

107
00:05:42,050 --> 00:05:43,890
It's the new Sabbath greatest hits.

108
00:05:44,050 --> 00:05:45,970
Well, if you'd like it, I can order it for you.

109
00:05:46,030 --> 00:05:46,810
No problem.

110
00:05:46,970 --> 00:05:48,470
Yeah, I'd really love that.

111
00:05:48,550 --> 00:05:50,590
You know, I'll give you my business card, okay?

112
00:05:50,690 --> 00:05:52,350
Don't give out contact info, I told you.

113
00:05:53,550 --> 00:05:56,250
Mr. Pacovsky here will give us his contact info, won't you?

114
00:05:57,250 --> 00:06:06,350
And he'll nicely sign a new payment plan so Mr. Hajek is happy and doesn't have to send the bad guys.

115
00:06:07,550 --> 00:06:08,650
Good day.

116
00:06:08,940 --> 00:06:09,780
Good day.

117
00:06:10,760 --> 00:06:11,400
No.

118
00:06:13,450 --> 00:06:14,550
Of course, it's you.

119
00:06:16,150 --> 00:06:16,850
Tommy Pacsy.

120
00:06:17,920 --> 00:06:18,780
Tommy Pacsy?

121
00:06:18,920 --> 00:06:20,600
The famous singer, of course.

122
00:06:21,600 --> 00:06:22,240
Don't know him.

123
00:06:22,440 --> 00:06:26,560
You don't remember? "Soak into me like rain, come blow with me like the wind."

124
00:06:26,660 --> 00:06:27,200
In '87.

125
00:06:27,880 --> 00:06:29,880
Third place at Intertalent.

126
00:06:29,880 --> 00:06:32,640
Right, so the man's a singer and he's famous.

127
00:06:33,250 --> 00:06:37,100
And he can't scrape together a lousy hundred grand for poor Mr. Hajek.

128
00:06:37,100 --> 00:06:37,840
Good day.

129
00:06:39,170 --> 00:06:41,390
Mr. Pacovsky, would you please sign for me?

130
00:06:41,530 --> 00:06:43,150
Excuse me, excuse me, I was here first.

131
00:06:43,750 --> 00:06:44,030
What?

132
00:06:44,370 --> 00:06:47,890
I already asked for that autograph 20 years ago at a concert in Slany.

133
00:06:47,970 --> 00:06:52,190
Some crazy woman pushed me aside back then, but today I won't let anyone push me.

134
00:06:52,270 --> 00:06:53,590
This is ridiculous, I'm here on business.

135
00:06:53,710 --> 00:06:55,570
Oh, and I'm here on vacation or what?

136
00:06:56,380 --> 00:06:58,940
Your last song still rings in my ears.

137
00:06:59,920 --> 00:07:01,300
You soak into me.

138
00:07:02,240 --> 00:07:04,740
You soak into me like rain.

139
00:07:04,780 --> 00:07:06,200
What's all this supposed to mean?

140
00:07:06,220 --> 00:07:08,540
Are we at some song recital or what?

141
00:07:08,700 --> 00:07:09,780
Just sign for me, please.

142
00:07:09,960 --> 00:07:12,060
Stop it, I'm allergic to this.

143
00:07:12,120 --> 00:07:14,240
If he's signing for anyone, it's me.

144
00:07:22,050 --> 00:07:23,350
We can leave if you want.

145
00:07:24,450 --> 00:07:27,430
Sure, but tomorrow.

146
00:07:27,750 --> 00:07:28,950
Tomorrow the bad ones come.

147
00:07:29,550 --> 00:07:30,450
No, in a week.

148
00:07:32,050 --> 00:07:32,850
Lubo, let's go.

149
00:07:33,550 --> 00:07:35,940
You said no names, Fanda.

150
00:07:35,940 --> 00:07:36,500
Tomorrow!

151
00:07:40,250 --> 00:07:40,810
Goodbye.

152
00:07:40,810 --> 00:07:43,330
See you tomorrow.

153
00:07:44,450 --> 00:07:46,850
Thank you so much, lady.

154
00:07:47,550 --> 00:07:49,150
Nice guys, you know.

155
00:07:49,650 --> 00:07:50,430
Especially the big one.

156
00:07:50,850 --> 00:07:53,950
I think, bro, I just got us a regular customer.

157
00:07:54,550 --> 00:07:55,110
A customer?

158
00:07:55,330 --> 00:07:55,530
Yeah.

159
00:07:56,750 --> 00:07:58,050
Those were debt collectors.

160
00:07:58,050 --> 00:08:00,150
They're not going to spend anything here.

161
00:08:00,150 --> 00:08:03,130
They'll come, take what they want, and smash whatever they don't take.

162
00:08:03,230 --> 00:08:05,930
And your CDs will be smashed to bits.

163
00:08:13,710 --> 00:08:14,270
Hi.

164
00:08:14,330 --> 00:08:14,770
Come on, Iva.

165
00:08:15,350 --> 00:08:17,370
I'll leave it open, bro's coming right back.

166
00:08:17,370 --> 00:08:19,030
You two are always together.

167
00:08:19,070 --> 00:08:20,910
Aren't you actually Siamese twins?

168
00:08:21,390 --> 00:08:23,630
Unfortunately not, someone would have to notice that.

169
00:08:24,750 --> 00:08:25,850
Iva, can you see me?

170
00:08:25,960 --> 00:08:26,520
What?

171
00:08:27,280 --> 00:08:28,460
I mean, can you see me?

172
00:08:29,260 --> 00:08:30,800
Did you hit your head?

173
00:08:31,420 --> 00:08:33,600
I feel like I'm invisible.

174
00:08:34,380 --> 00:08:37,260
When I walk down the street, people look right through me.

175
00:08:37,340 --> 00:08:39,340
When I say hello to someone, they don't answer.

176
00:08:39,750 --> 00:08:41,180
My classmates ignore me.

177
00:08:41,180 --> 00:08:42,880
Only ticket inspectors notice me.

178
00:08:42,980 --> 00:08:44,480
But you're just imagining it.

179
00:08:45,250 --> 00:08:49,730
You're just the quiet type, but otherwise you're a perfectly visible girl.

180
00:08:49,730 --> 00:08:50,190
Hi, Iva.

181
00:08:51,350 --> 00:08:52,350
Have you seen Sasha?

182
00:08:53,750 --> 00:08:56,080
My problem is you have a nutcase for a brother.

183
00:08:56,080 --> 00:08:56,740
What is it?

184
00:08:57,500 --> 00:08:58,420
It was a joke, right?

185
00:08:58,740 --> 00:08:59,940
But it wasn't a joke.

186
00:09:00,120 --> 00:09:01,640
Can't you see your sister's depressed?

187
00:09:02,250 --> 00:09:02,950
I can't.

188
00:09:03,350 --> 00:09:05,050
Iva, have you seen Sasha with depression?

189
00:09:06,380 --> 00:09:08,480
Or maybe it's an underdeveloped personality.

190
00:09:08,520 --> 00:09:09,840
Everyone notices Lexa right away.

191
00:09:10,060 --> 00:09:11,680
Yeah, because he's abnormal.

192
00:09:11,760 --> 00:09:13,100
But you're normal.

193
00:09:13,260 --> 00:09:14,720
Normal, but invisible.

194
00:09:16,110 --> 00:09:16,630
What is it?

195
00:09:17,030 --> 00:09:17,470
Nothing.

196
00:09:18,850 --> 00:09:22,150
Can you give me a moment? These are sensitive matters.

197
00:09:26,350 --> 00:09:28,450
Or, and this is the worst part, I start telling someone something and they start dealing with something completely different.

198
00:09:28,750 --> 00:09:46,330
Like the other day I woke up Mom and I told her what should I do, that I feel lonely, that all the girls my age already have boyfriends, that they shave their legs, that they go to discos and at those discos they meet those boys, and nobody notices me even though I shave too.

199
00:09:46,750 --> 00:09:48,350
And I asked what I should do.

200
00:09:48,450 --> 00:09:49,750
And she took a deep breath and said...

201
00:09:50,560 --> 00:09:51,600
Lexa, what are you doing there?

202
00:09:52,250 --> 00:09:53,550
That's exactly what she said.

203
00:09:54,470 --> 00:09:55,090
Nothing?

204
00:09:56,850 --> 00:09:58,150
Don't say nothing.

205
00:09:58,850 --> 00:10:05,650
Look, I know you're attracted to me, that you're obsessed with me, but what you're doing borders on a psychological disorder.

206
00:10:06,150 --> 00:10:07,150
What kind of disorder?

207
00:10:07,550 --> 00:10:08,750
Lexa, show me your hand.

208
00:10:09,140 --> 00:10:09,760
Which one?

209
00:10:10,250 --> 00:10:17,950
Lexa, why do you have Ozzak's underwear?

210
00:10:19,850 --> 00:10:21,650
I wanted to help you.

211
00:10:22,180 --> 00:10:22,740
Hang up laundry.

212
00:10:26,350 --> 00:10:28,850
Oh fine, then please, help.

213
00:10:31,850 --> 00:10:33,050
Sorry, what were you saying?

214
00:10:40,550 --> 00:10:42,160
Simona, one more time.

215
00:10:42,550 --> 00:10:50,800
Tommy, if you would one more time, I mean on stage, soak into me like rain.

216
00:10:52,650 --> 00:10:55,320
Madam, I'm not soaking today.

217
00:10:56,050 --> 00:10:57,650
And I'll soak into you.

218
00:10:59,260 --> 00:11:01,020
I see you keep lowering your standards.

219
00:11:01,440 --> 00:11:02,620
What do you need?

220
00:11:03,150 --> 00:11:04,640
A hundred grand or vodka.

221
00:11:04,750 --> 00:11:08,180
Tom, are you still mad at me?

222
00:11:08,550 --> 00:11:10,050
I did everything right this time.

223
00:11:10,450 --> 00:11:12,350
I quit show business, put my money into a shop, raised a girl, hired my brother.

224
00:11:16,440 --> 00:11:18,320
He did everything right and hired Ozzak.

225
00:11:18,580 --> 00:11:19,420
I'm cutting you off.

226
00:11:21,550 --> 00:11:22,860
Then tell me what to do.

227
00:11:22,950 --> 00:11:24,220
First of all, smile.

228
00:11:24,220 --> 00:11:25,280
Everything goes better with a smile.

229
00:11:26,540 --> 00:11:27,100
Well?

230
00:11:27,650 --> 00:11:28,550
Lexa?

231
00:11:29,350 --> 00:11:30,750
He's completely lost it.

232
00:11:31,350 --> 00:11:33,750
Can you hang white laundry with colored?

233
00:11:35,650 --> 00:11:38,950
Lexa, is that some former pop star too?

234
00:11:39,150 --> 00:11:41,010
No, that's my crazy son.

235
00:11:41,010 --> 00:11:42,190
Takes after his father.

236
00:11:42,190 --> 00:11:44,450
See, your ex is doing well for himself.

237
00:11:45,150 --> 00:11:48,340
He's doing well alright, but with someone else.

238
00:11:48,350 --> 00:11:51,350
He's living it up overseas.

239
00:11:52,350 --> 00:11:54,680
Go to Gott and let him help you.

240
00:11:54,750 --> 00:11:56,450
Beg from Karel Gott?

241
00:11:56,550 --> 00:11:57,650
Never!

242
00:11:59,440 --> 00:12:00,220
Hard to resist, huh?

243
00:12:01,950 --> 00:12:05,550
Well, let's keep her here as a jukebox.

244
00:12:07,750 --> 00:12:11,550
Don't worry, my darlings, I'll hide you and they won't find you.

245
00:12:14,650 --> 00:12:15,650
Hey Uncle, what's going on down there?

246
00:12:17,120 --> 00:12:17,720
Don't even ask.

247
00:12:18,350 --> 00:12:21,160
Some debt collectors want to wreck the place?

248
00:12:21,160 --> 00:12:21,540
How?

249
00:12:21,820 --> 00:12:22,500
I don't know.

250
00:12:23,100 --> 00:12:24,820
They came in and at first they didn't seem bad.

251
00:12:24,880 --> 00:12:26,480
The big one was even interested in Sabbath.

252
00:12:27,350 --> 00:12:32,200
Yeah, if we don't get 100 grand soon, they'll smash my CDs.

253
00:12:32,200 --> 00:12:33,020
That's seriously messed up.

254
00:12:36,030 --> 00:12:36,430
Yeah.

255
00:12:37,150 --> 00:12:38,250
What is that, Mr. Ozzak?

256
00:12:38,450 --> 00:12:40,250
Nothing children's eyes should see.

257
00:12:40,350 --> 00:12:40,750
Porn.

258
00:12:40,950 --> 00:12:41,350
Cool.

259
00:12:43,060 --> 00:12:43,460
Yeah.

260
00:12:45,950 --> 00:12:46,850
Was your dad gay?

261
00:12:47,550 --> 00:12:49,850
Keep your mouth shut.

262
00:12:52,950 --> 00:12:56,850
I knew Dad used to make a living in a weird way, but this weird?

263
00:12:57,050 --> 00:12:58,750
What is he wearing?

264
00:13:00,030 --> 00:13:00,690
Gay clothes.

265
00:13:02,530 --> 00:13:03,850
What else is there, Mr. Ozzak?

266
00:13:03,950 --> 00:13:04,690
Nothing interesting.

267
00:13:05,550 --> 00:13:08,150
The only decent thing in there is that dartboard.

268
00:13:09,810 --> 00:13:11,290
So what else have you got?

269
00:13:12,920 --> 00:13:15,080
I don't think you're ready for this yet.

270
00:13:15,080 --> 00:13:17,850
Uncle, unpack it or I'll tell Dad where you hide Gott.

271
00:13:22,950 --> 00:13:24,750
Some kind of chain.

272
00:13:24,840 --> 00:13:25,400
CDs.

273
00:13:25,960 --> 00:13:26,520
Vitamins?

274
00:13:26,780 --> 00:13:27,340
Vitamins.

275
00:13:27,420 --> 00:13:29,140
Kids' piggy banks were drained by those.

276
00:13:30,150 --> 00:13:32,180
An original Michal David, hide it.

277
00:13:32,450 --> 00:13:34,340
Never speak that name again.

278
00:13:35,050 --> 00:13:35,850
And what's this?

279
00:13:35,870 --> 00:13:36,430
Betamax.

280
00:13:37,250 --> 00:13:39,150
It says "Two Little Wings" on it.

281
00:13:39,150 --> 00:13:39,430
Are they there?

282
00:13:39,910 --> 00:13:40,470
They're not.

283
00:13:40,670 --> 00:13:41,090
See.

284
00:13:45,150 --> 00:13:46,750
You were never supposed to find this.

285
00:13:47,050 --> 00:13:47,690
I know what that is.

286
00:13:48,150 --> 00:13:49,950
You used to burn CDs on it.

287
00:13:50,310 --> 00:13:51,330
The porn is on that.

288
00:14:01,540 --> 00:14:02,780
Welcome to my place.

289
00:14:02,800 --> 00:14:05,740
For the inner circle, press one.

290
00:14:05,820 --> 00:14:07,580
For the outer circle, press two.

291
00:14:07,760 --> 00:14:08,260
Karel?

292
00:14:08,460 --> 00:14:13,200
If you'd like to hear my interpretation of world history, press three.

293
00:14:15,550 --> 00:14:24,250
If you'd like to leave a message, wait for my high C. Hi Karel, this is Tomy Pacsy.

294
00:14:24,750 --> 00:14:25,450
Remember...

295
00:14:25,470 --> 00:14:27,310
How we used to party in Sopot.

296
00:14:27,950 --> 00:14:29,470
Please, I've got a problem.

297
00:14:30,050 --> 00:14:32,230
I need to borrow some money.

298
00:14:32,390 --> 00:14:35,730
I will listen to your message on Sunday, when I rest.

299
00:14:36,150 --> 00:14:41,850
If you'd like advice for today, press the star key.

300
00:14:44,350 --> 00:14:47,150
Never borrow from friends.

301
00:14:59,550 --> 00:15:02,010
The eighties, those were terrible times.

302
00:15:02,010 --> 00:15:03,390
Yeah, Depeche Mode fans.

303
00:15:04,510 --> 00:15:05,350
Vitezslav Vavra.

304
00:15:06,050 --> 00:15:07,050
Marketa Muchova.

305
00:15:07,250 --> 00:15:08,250
Pavel Hornak.

306
00:15:09,110 --> 00:15:09,630
Spartakiad.

307
00:15:10,350 --> 00:15:11,450
Yeah, we know him.

308
00:15:11,450 --> 00:15:13,270
We learned all this in school, right?

309
00:15:13,730 --> 00:15:16,530
No freedom, oppression, Gorbachev, then they locked up Havel.

310
00:15:16,570 --> 00:15:17,570
Then they burned Palach.

311
00:15:17,790 --> 00:15:18,470
There was a revolution.

312
00:15:18,790 --> 00:15:19,310
Velvet.

313
00:15:21,250 --> 00:15:26,050
I can see you've got that down, but what's in the textbooks isn't what matters.

314
00:15:26,550 --> 00:15:31,550
Just one document like this is enough to understand what brainwashing was.

315
00:15:36,750 --> 00:15:41,400
You soak into me like rain and I'll soak into you.

316
00:15:41,400 --> 00:15:47,840
Such happiness you won't find, you'd go all the way to heaven.

317
00:15:47,840 --> 00:15:55,150
You'd carry me away like a hurricane, I wouldn't care that I don't know where.

318
00:15:55,350 --> 00:15:59,150
You soak into me like rain.

319
00:16:04,650 --> 00:16:07,550
You saw nothing and you remember nothing.

320
00:16:08,450 --> 00:16:10,250
I actually kind of liked it.

321
00:16:10,550 --> 00:16:11,550
He needed money.

322
00:16:12,450 --> 00:16:14,950
Yeah, but what a disgrace.

323
00:16:16,150 --> 00:16:16,650
A disgrace.

324
00:16:17,750 --> 00:16:21,050
Lexa, what did you say people spend the most on online?

325
00:16:21,350 --> 00:16:22,250
I don't know, but I spend on dirty stuff.

326
00:16:23,430 --> 00:16:24,310
Dirty stuff?

327
00:16:24,710 --> 00:16:26,010
Nothing gets burned.

328
00:16:26,850 --> 00:16:30,510
People are perverts and all this stuff can definitely sell well.

329
00:16:30,750 --> 00:16:34,050
Sure, people buy all kinds of crazy stuff these days, you'd be surprised.

330
00:16:34,050 --> 00:16:35,690
Like photos of my sister in the shower.

331
00:16:36,470 --> 00:16:37,030
What?

332
00:16:38,780 --> 00:16:39,340
What?

333
00:16:40,730 --> 00:16:41,290
What?

334
00:16:41,410 --> 00:16:43,070
That can't be, you little brat.

335
00:16:43,130 --> 00:16:45,050
Jesus, buddy, what are you doing here?

336
00:16:45,310 --> 00:16:49,910
Hey Standa, look, this is really embarrassing, but I need to borrow some money.

337
00:16:50,050 --> 00:16:52,410
Sure, how much do you need?

338
00:16:53,850 --> 00:16:55,350
Well, exactly, 100 thousand.

339
00:16:56,950 --> 00:17:02,550
I really would, I really would, in '88 you pulled me off the shovel.

340
00:17:03,150 --> 00:17:05,850
But I don't have it.

341
00:17:06,350 --> 00:17:07,550
I'm expecting expenses.

342
00:17:07,910 --> 00:17:09,010
Yeah, meet them.

343
00:17:09,010 --> 00:17:12,050
Majda, Lenka, and Bolenka with Veronika.

344
00:17:23,450 --> 00:17:24,150
This camera.

345
00:17:24,450 --> 00:17:25,540
How do you get it online?

346
00:17:25,650 --> 00:17:26,650
Easy.

347
00:17:27,250 --> 00:17:31,370
We take photos, connect to the computer, upload to the server, add a comment and wait for the first post.

348
00:17:31,370 --> 00:17:31,690
Got it?

349
00:17:33,950 --> 00:17:35,270
Hey, what's this here?

350
00:17:35,270 --> 00:17:35,710
What?

351
00:17:35,710 --> 00:17:38,150
This label that says "Sexy Lexa."

352
00:17:38,490 --> 00:17:38,930
Nothing.

353
00:17:39,750 --> 00:17:40,590
Just some link.

354
00:17:40,750 --> 00:17:42,570
And why is my photo on it?

355
00:17:42,950 --> 00:17:44,150
It was already there.

356
00:17:44,970 --> 00:17:46,070
That's our shower.

357
00:17:47,750 --> 00:17:50,350
Lexa, how could you put naked photos of your sister online?

358
00:17:50,850 --> 00:17:53,880
It was easy, I just connected to the computer and uploaded to the server.

359
00:17:54,250 --> 00:17:57,550
And why is there so much writing in that weird script under my picture?

360
00:17:57,850 --> 00:18:00,350
Classic, Vietnamese discussion forum.

361
00:18:00,950 --> 00:18:03,450
If you can get rich on photos anywhere.

362
00:18:03,950 --> 00:18:07,450
I mean, on these record collector sites, that's the place.

363
00:18:07,610 --> 00:18:09,370
Someone is discussing me there?

364
00:18:09,530 --> 00:18:10,670
What are they saying?

365
00:18:11,230 --> 00:18:12,130
They're pretty complimentary.

366
00:18:12,650 --> 00:18:14,850
What are you talking about, since when do you speak Vietnamese?

367
00:18:15,150 --> 00:18:17,190
What are automatic translators for?

368
00:18:17,450 --> 00:18:19,450
Sasha, click the green circle.

369
00:18:20,550 --> 00:18:22,950
I would like not just look but also touch.

370
00:18:23,150 --> 00:18:24,270
What do you mean?

371
00:18:24,990 --> 00:18:25,930
Don't worry, Sasha.

372
00:18:25,930 --> 00:18:27,470
There's probably something better too.

373
00:18:27,750 --> 00:18:28,910
Well, like that one there.

374
00:18:29,030 --> 00:18:31,550
She so pretty, I cry right away.

375
00:18:31,650 --> 00:18:32,130
See?

376
00:18:32,310 --> 00:18:34,770
Well, "cry" has multiple meanings in Vietnamese.

377
00:18:35,650 --> 00:18:37,730
I cry for you four times in a row.

378
00:18:38,230 --> 00:18:39,730
Let me explain that to you right away, Sasha.

379
00:18:40,450 --> 00:18:42,750
I very much like your water rodent.

380
00:18:44,150 --> 00:18:46,150
I guess they really do like me.

381
00:18:46,350 --> 00:18:53,160
Well, it's true that the Vietnamese might buy it.

382
00:18:53,480 --> 00:18:55,760
Not just the Vietnamese, the whole world shops there.

383
00:18:56,250 --> 00:18:57,760
Sasha is upstairs chatting with them right now.

384
00:18:57,950 --> 00:18:58,950
Which Sasha?

385
00:18:59,650 --> 00:19:00,340
She's my sister.

386
00:19:00,650 --> 00:19:01,650
You have a sister?

387
00:19:02,200 --> 00:19:03,220
Sure, my twin.

388
00:19:03,380 --> 00:19:04,600
Bring her by sometime.

389
00:19:09,850 --> 00:19:10,750
Bro, so what?

390
00:19:11,150 --> 00:19:11,950
Got the cash?

391
00:19:13,380 --> 00:19:14,020
Don't worry, Dad.

392
00:19:14,550 --> 00:19:17,650
We're trying something and if it works out, you'll have enough to pay.

393
00:19:18,450 --> 00:19:19,650
Enough to pay?

394
00:19:19,910 --> 00:19:20,310
How?

395
00:19:22,150 --> 00:19:23,250
Legally.

396
00:19:23,550 --> 00:19:25,850
Let the girl know how cruel the world is.

397
00:19:31,450 --> 00:19:31,950
Can someone explain what's going on here?

398
00:19:37,260 --> 00:19:40,080
Now we can, we managed to sell your old junk over the internet.

399
00:19:40,740 --> 00:19:41,560
What junk?

400
00:19:41,680 --> 00:19:43,900
You know, that suitcase full of stuff in the hole in the wall.

401
00:19:46,250 --> 00:19:46,750
What?

402
00:19:49,350 --> 00:19:52,450
You sold my personal belongings.

403
00:19:53,850 --> 00:19:56,590
Do you have any idea what those things are worth?

404
00:19:56,590 --> 00:19:57,710
More than a hundred thousand.

405
00:19:57,850 --> 00:19:58,890
A hundred thousand for that?

406
00:19:59,350 --> 00:20:03,170
A hundred thousand for a whole human life, for my dreams, for my memories?

407
00:20:03,170 --> 00:20:04,210
A hundred thousand?

408
00:20:05,240 --> 00:20:06,580
Did you say a hundred thousand?

409
00:20:06,900 --> 00:20:07,380
Yeah.

410
00:20:08,010 --> 00:20:09,750
In that case, we're saved!

411
00:20:09,750 --> 00:20:17,340
That's incredible!

412
00:20:17,340 --> 00:20:18,080
Where are you?

413
00:20:18,320 --> 00:20:19,500
One of my fans.

414
00:20:19,720 --> 00:20:22,680
I just made the best purchase of my life.

415
00:20:22,820 --> 00:20:24,060
What purchases?

416
00:20:24,280 --> 00:20:26,740
I bought relics from your artistic career.

417
00:20:26,780 --> 00:20:28,200
Everything's there.

418
00:20:28,220 --> 00:20:30,780
Posters, genuine Michal David CDs.

419
00:20:31,950 --> 00:20:34,680
I'd like to donate it all to you.

420
00:20:34,680 --> 00:20:38,440
Throw out this junk and make your own museum here.

421
00:20:38,460 --> 00:20:40,540
People will come here like to Graceland.

422
00:20:40,780 --> 00:20:42,740
Wait, you're the one who bought it?

423
00:20:43,350 --> 00:20:43,850
Yes, it was almost free.

424
00:20:45,200 --> 00:20:46,900
A hundred thousand Vietnamese dong.

425
00:20:47,120 --> 00:20:48,620
How much is that in crowns?

426
00:20:49,250 --> 00:20:50,250
About a hundred.

427
00:20:50,420 --> 00:20:51,560
You idiot.

428
00:20:52,650 --> 00:20:55,550
A hundred crowns for my entire past?

429
00:20:56,150 --> 00:20:58,550
Doesn't my life have more value?

430
00:20:58,950 --> 00:21:00,760
What should I say, Mr. Pacovsky?

431
00:21:01,150 --> 00:21:03,450
Such fantastic shower photos.

432
00:21:03,850 --> 00:21:06,350
For a lousy two crowns.

433
00:21:07,050 --> 00:21:08,550
Aren't you happy?

434
00:21:08,550 --> 00:21:10,250
Miserable woman.

435
00:21:10,850 --> 00:21:14,450
In a few hours the debt collectors will be here and I might lose my life.

436
00:21:14,750 --> 00:21:17,650
At least she knows it's not worth much.

437
00:21:19,350 --> 00:21:20,550
I'm still here.

438
00:21:24,950 --> 00:21:26,960
Here we are, and now it's getting serious.

439
00:21:27,350 --> 00:21:28,520
Who doesn't belong here?

440
00:21:28,520 --> 00:21:28,660
Out!

441
00:21:29,750 --> 00:21:31,050
Out, scram!

442
00:21:34,400 --> 00:21:36,660
So what are we playing today, Lubo?

443
00:21:37,350 --> 00:21:38,850
You said no names, Fanda.

444
00:21:39,150 --> 00:21:40,850
Shut up and show me the bag.

445
00:21:50,340 --> 00:21:50,860
Golf?

446
00:21:52,360 --> 00:21:53,660
I prefer baseball.

447
00:21:55,880 --> 00:21:57,260
I got you those Sabbath CDs.

448
00:22:03,330 --> 00:22:04,450
I told you what?

449
00:22:04,690 --> 00:22:05,510
What did I tell you?

450
00:22:05,570 --> 00:22:06,570
What did I tell them, Lubo, what?

451
00:22:06,870 --> 00:22:08,230
You told them, Fanda.

452
00:22:09,030 --> 00:22:12,310
Exactly, I told you the bad guys would come.

453
00:22:12,310 --> 00:22:13,730
And here they are, see?

454
00:22:13,950 --> 00:22:15,710
All done here, let's go to the store.

455
00:22:16,750 --> 00:22:17,850
I know you from somewhere.

456
00:22:19,550 --> 00:22:22,830
Apparently this isn't your first experience with seizure.

457
00:22:22,830 --> 00:22:24,770
Colleague, let's continue the asset inventory.

458
00:22:25,310 --> 00:22:27,810
Excuse me, but what's this supposed to mean?

459
00:22:27,930 --> 00:22:30,070
Mr. Pacovsky owes an enormous amount of money.

460
00:22:30,130 --> 00:22:30,870
Yes, he does.

461
00:22:30,970 --> 00:22:36,750
But to the state. If you represent a private creditor, contact the bankruptcy trustee.

462
00:22:36,850 --> 00:22:37,990
But Mr. Hajek...

463
00:22:37,990 --> 00:22:38,830
Will have to wait.

464
00:22:39,150 --> 00:22:44,510
First in line is the Ministry of Finance, the bank, the Ministry of Interior, the Ministry of... Debts.

465
00:22:44,650 --> 00:22:45,730
Are those baseball bats yours?

466
00:22:46,550 --> 00:22:47,290
Those are ours.

467
00:22:47,290 --> 00:22:49,110
And this junk?

468
00:22:49,110 --> 00:22:53,250
Is there any business connection between you and Mr. Pacovsky here?

469
00:22:53,260 --> 00:22:57,600
No, no, no, we have absolutely nothing to do with this.

470
00:22:57,720 --> 00:23:04,380
We're just, you know, here by chance, just, just passing through, and now we're leaving, right, goodbye.

471
00:23:04,760 --> 00:23:07,420
Gentlemen, gentlemen, and that car outside, is it yours?

472
00:23:07,580 --> 00:23:09,360
That's Lubomir's here, goodbye.

473
00:23:13,350 --> 00:23:14,150
That's that.

474
00:23:14,650 --> 00:23:16,480
Marcelka, you're a genius.

475
00:23:16,480 --> 00:23:17,660
And not just in this.

476
00:23:19,850 --> 00:23:21,350
No way.

477
00:23:21,850 --> 00:23:23,390
Not a scratch.

478
00:23:23,510 --> 00:23:26,690
I always said Sabbath is the toughest band in the world.

479
00:23:26,790 --> 00:23:28,730
We handled that beautifully.

480
00:23:31,650 --> 00:23:34,090
That's great, friends, but I still need a hundred thousand.

481
00:23:44,650 --> 00:23:46,750
This will be tougher.

482
00:23:48,250 --> 00:24:00,850
So this is what it looks like.

483
00:24:04,850 --> 00:24:10,950
You know, sometimes I have these unlikely nightmares about poverty.

484
00:24:11,650 --> 00:24:15,040
So I came to see what it looks like in real life.

485
00:24:17,150 --> 00:24:20,010
Look, Karel, if you came to make fun of me, then...

486
00:24:21,850 --> 00:24:23,550
I came to give you advice.

487
00:24:26,650 --> 00:24:28,150
If it's free.

488
00:24:29,950 --> 00:24:32,850
Every thing has two sides.

489
00:24:36,450 --> 00:24:43,260
Look, I once painted my first painting on a dartboard just like this.

490
00:24:43,650 --> 00:24:45,650
I was alone in a late-night arcade.

491
00:24:45,850 --> 00:24:53,150
And I happened to have a beautiful, inspiring blonde within reach.

492
00:25:02,050 --> 00:25:03,780
Don't be servile, Marianne.

493
00:25:06,750 --> 00:25:08,250
You calm down too, Rene.

494
00:25:11,550 --> 00:25:16,450
Pity I don't remember what happened to that dartboard.

495
00:25:16,750 --> 00:25:18,850
I may have given it to someone.

496
00:25:21,750 --> 00:25:23,630
It would be worth millions now.

497
00:25:26,850 --> 00:25:28,010
Well, I have to fly.

498
00:25:28,010 --> 00:25:28,590
Bye.

499
00:25:32,850 --> 00:25:35,050
Oh, and one more thing, don't forget.

500
00:25:35,250 --> 00:25:37,350
Every thing has two sides.

501
00:25:38,250 --> 00:25:39,650
How about I thank you, Karel?

502
00:25:39,950 --> 00:25:41,250
Will you come by again sometime?

503
00:25:42,050 --> 00:25:45,250
My ways are mysterious.

504
00:25:53,250 --> 00:25:53,950
He exists.

505
00:26:01,550 --> 00:26:03,250
Ozzak, where did you get that dartboard?

506
00:26:04,590 --> 00:26:07,720
It was with your suitcase of stuff from the eighties.

507
00:26:16,050 --> 00:26:18,850
And for a moment I thought miracles were real.

508
00:26:23,450 --> 00:26:24,890
That woman kept making me nervous.

509
00:26:24,890 --> 00:26:37,320
But I want a new dartboard.
